<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>A small studio with strong opinions about clarity.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      DesignShifu was founded on a simple bet: design is the cheapest growth lever most companies never pull. We&rsquo;ve spent the last six years pulling it for our clients.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container container-narrow prose">
    <h2>Our point of view</h2>
    <p>
      Most design work fails because the brief is wrong. Teams ask for a redesign when they need positioning. They ask for a logo when they need a customer. We start by asking which decision the design has to make easier, then we work backwards from there.
    </p>
    <p>
      We&rsquo;re partial to short engagements with clear deliverables. We&rsquo;d rather ship something useful in two weeks than something polished in two quarters. If you need a 90-page brand bible, we are not the right studio.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-values">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we operate</p>
      <h2>Four rules we won&rsquo;t bend.</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="value-grid">
      <li>
        <h3>Ship the obvious thing first</h3>
        <p>The boring 80% always beats the clever 100%. We design what users actually need before we design what would look good in a portfolio.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Strategy is a deliverable</h3>
        <p>Every engagement starts with a one-page strategy doc. If we can&rsquo;t write the why in one page, we&rsquo;re not ready to design.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Async by default</h3>
        <p>We protect maker time. Most communication happens in Notion and Slack threads, not on calls. Calls are reserved for decisions.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>One throat to choke</h3>
        <p>You get one senior designer as your partner from kickoff to launch. No account managers, no handoffs, no junior shadow team.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

